dcterms:description: ERA5 is a state-of-the-art atmospheric reanalysis dataset produced by the European Centre for Medium-Range Weather Forecasts (ECMWF). It provides hourly data at a spatial resolution of 0.25° × 0.25° on a single pressure level, including various climate variables such as temperature, dewpoint temperature, wind components, mean sea level pressure, and total precipitation.
dcterms:title: ERA5

dcterms:description: MERRA2 is an atmospheric reanalysis dataset that provides data at a spatial resolution of 0.5° × 0.625°. It includes climate variables such as total precipitation, surface wind speed, surface air temperature, and surface wind components.
dcterms:title: MERRA2

dcterms:description: The NOAA Climate Forecast System Reanalysis (CFSR) is a global coupled atmosphere-ocean-land surface-sea ice system dataset that provides data at a spatial resolution of 0.5° × 0.5°. It includes climate variables such as precipitable water, downward longwave radiation flux, surface temperature, and pressure at mean sea level.
dcterms:title: NOAA CFSR

dcterms:description: NorESM is based on the second version of the Norwegian Earth System Model (NorESM2), which is a coupled Earth System Model. The dataset includes temperature at the surface and is based on two different runs with different resolutions, providing data for various climate scenarios.
dcterms:title: NorESM
